com.camerontec.catalys.core.message

Class MessageIntegrityException

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Throwable
      • java.lang.Exception
        • com.camerontec.catalys.core.message.MessageIntegrityException
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable

    public class MessageIntegrityException
extends Exception
    Indicates that a problem was detected during the integrity check of FIX message. Currently the only integrity checks for inbound FIX messages are:
    • Message digest (signature) validation if encryption is enabled.
    See Also:

    • Constructor Detail

      • MessageIntegrityException

        public MessageIntegrityException(int code,
                                 IFIXMessage fixMessage,
                                 String message,
                                 int msgSeqNum,
                                 String msgType)
        This constructor allows you to associate a number of extra FIX message values with the exception.

        These extra values are those commonly used in the FIX Session level Reject message.

        Parameters:
        code - Indicates the cause of the integrity message exception.
        fixMessage - FIX message which cause tthe integrity message exception.
        message - Any text associated with the exception.
        msgSeqNum - Message sequence number of related message - null if unknown.
        msgType - Message type of related message - null if unknown.
